The forest behind the stone gate is called '''Sonohyan-utaki'''. This utaki was a sacred place where the king would always pray before departing on journeys. Additionally, the {{ill|Kikoe-ōgimi|ja|聞得大君|qq=draft|qq=draft}} performed her first prayer here upon assuming her position, making it a national {{ill|sacred site|ja|聖地|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The shrine enshrines the deity "Tanoue no Sonohiyabu" from Iheya Island, which was closely linked to the ruling {{ill|Shō family|ja|尚氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Originally, it was a much larger forest, but parts of it have since been used for a school, leaving only a portion intact.

