'''Sonohyan-utaki''' (園比屋武御嶽) is an {{ill|utaki|ja|御嶽|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/utaki|qq=}}, or sacred site, from the 16th century during the {{ill|Ryukyu Kingdom|ja|琉球王国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ryukyu Kingdom|qq=}}'s {{ill|King Shō Shin|ja|尚真王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/King Shō Shin|qq=}} era. It is located in {{ill|Shuri, Naha|ja|首里|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shuri, Naha|qq=}}, {{ill|Naha, Okinawa|ja|那覇市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Naha, Okinawa|qq=}}, Okinawa Prefecture, and is designated as an Okinawa Prefecture Historic Site.

== Overview ==
The forest behind the stone gate is called '''Sonohyan-utaki'''. This utaki was a sacred place where the king would always pray before departing on journeys. Additionally, the {{ill|Kikoe-ōgimi|ja|聞得大君|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kikoe-ōgimi|qq=}} performed her first prayer here upon assuming her position, making it a national {{ill|sacred site|ja|聖地|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/sacred site|qq=}}. The shrine enshrines the deity "Tanoue no Sonohiyabu" from Iheya Island, which was closely linked to the ruling {{ill|Shō family|ja|尚氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shō family|qq=}}. Originally, it was a much larger forest, but parts of it have since been used for a school, leaving only a portion intact.

== Sonohyan-utaki Ishimon ==
Located between {{ill|Kankaimon|ja|歓会門|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kankaimon|qq=}} and {{ill|Shureimon|ja|守礼門|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shureimon|qq=}} at {{ill|Shuri Castle|ja|首里城|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shuri Castle|qq=}}, the '''Sonohyan-utaki Ishimon''' (園比屋武御嶽石門) serves as the {{ill|Haisho|ja|拝所|lt=worship site|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Haisho|qq=}} of the utaki. This stone gate was built in [[1519]] during the reign of {{ill|King Shō Shin|ja|尚真|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/King Shō Shin|qq=}}, the third monarch of the {{ill|Second Shō Dynasty|ja|第二尚氏王統|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Second Shō Dynasty|qq=}}. It is said to have been established by {{ill|Sai Tō|ja|西塘|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sai Tō|qq=}}, who was brought to Shuri by {{ill|Ōzato Aji|ja|大里親方|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōzato Aji|qq=}} after the {{ill|Oyake Akahachi Rebellion|ja|オヤケアカハチの乱|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oyake Akahachi Rebellion|qq=}} in 1500, during which the royal army was sent to the {{ill|Yaeyama Islands|ja|八重山列島|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yaeyama Islands|qq=}}.

